-- Inter Milan Beats Seongnam Ilhwa 3-0 to Reach Club World Cup Soccer Final
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2010-12-15T19:00:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-15/inter-milan-beats-seongnam-ilhwa-3-0-to-reach-club-world-cup-soccer-final.html
Inter Milan defeated South Korea’s
Seongnam Ilhwa 3-0 to advance to the final of soccer’s FIFA  Club
World Cup  in Abu Dhabi.  Dejan Stankovic ,  Javier Zanetti  and  Diego Milito  scored to
send European champion Inter to the Dec. 18 final against TP
Mazembe Englebert of Congo.  European clubs have won the past three editions of the 10-
year-old tournament contested by the champions of the
continental soccer federations.  TP Mazembe defeated Brazil’s Sport Club Internacional 2-0
yesterday to become the first African team to reach the title
match.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Bob Bensch  in London at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at   celser@bloomberg.net . 